    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="768"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d768">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/23437.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Special Commissioners</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Niagara Falls</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 22, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Acting upon your telegram of 21st, we inquired of the Mediators whether they
                    would not consider it advisable to renew the invitation to the
                    Constitutionalists to send commissioners without attempting to define the scope
                    of what was to be discussed and without reference to suspension of hostilities.
                    After extended discussion the Mediators answered, individually and as a body,
                    that as the Constitutionalists had definitely; declined the invitation
                    personally extended to them and had declined to recognize anything except the
                    issues between General Huerta and the United States as appropriate to mediation,
                    all questions relative to reforms to be for the Constitutionalists themselves to
                    determine, it would not be consistent with the honor of the nations represented
                    by the Mediators nor with the dignity or prestige of the mediation itself to
                    renew the invitation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Commissioners</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
